  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">WIR III: Workshops for Integration and Room of Encounter</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims at supporting youngsters from the Chechen as well as other communities in the development of their identity and in the process of integration within Austria by providing them the opportunity to value and reflect on their roots. Further, the project wants to support participants in the development of necessary skills and strategies to recognize and challenge potential tendencies of radicalization. The overarching objective is to contribute to enhance social cohesion as a mean to prevent radicalization. Co-teaching teams, composed of specially trained intercultural mediators from the Chechen community and expert youth workers as well as an IOM project coordinator, will conduct two series of workshops in the participating cities, in which the youngsters&#x2019; experiences in an intercultural setting will be discussed. The workshops will address the history and current state of affairs in both Chechnya, other countries of origin and Austria and will increase beneficiaries&#x2019; media literacy and social skills in intercultural communication and conflict management, they will also have the opportunity to create their own media products. Other youngsters, among other further project participants will be trained as multipliers and supported to conduct school workshops. Along with intercultural mediators, they will act as role model within and outside their communities.</narrative>
  </description>
